author: COMSOL
description:
This model exemplifies the analysis of flow around a solar panel and the corresponding structural displacement due to the strong wind load. The solar panel studied is located in a regularly spaced array of identical panels, implying that periodic flow conditions can be applied in the streamwise direction. The model solves for the flow field for a free stream velocity of 25Â m/s and computes the resulting structural stresses and displacements.

NOTE: The model requires the CFD Module and the Structural Mechanics Module.
